cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically with word embeddings, which are widely used in NLP. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses machine learning techniques for debiasing word embeddings, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with bias in society, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper presents experiments to support its claims, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
